ulati\n|April 1995\n|May 1996\n|[[9th Deccan Horse]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|Chandra Sekhar\n|June 1996\n|September 1997\n|[[4 Gorkha Rifles|2/4 Gorkha Rifles]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=Padmanabhan may be new Army Chief |url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2000/20000801/main5.htm |website= |publisher=Tribune India}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|Surjit Singh\n|October 1997\n|September 2000\n|[[Dogra Regiment]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=\"Shortage of officers may continue\" |url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2001/20011013/windows/main2.htm |website= |publisher=Tribune India}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|P S Joshi\n|October 2000\n|September 2001\n|[[8 Gorkha Rifles|1/8 Gorkha Rifles]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=First IDS chief Lt Gen Joshi dies |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/First-IDS-chief-Lt-Gen-Joshi-dies/articleshow/4729577.cms |website=Times of India |publisher=Times of India}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|D S Chauhan\n|October 2001\n|December 2003\n|[[Madras Regiment]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=New Army Vice-Chief |url=http://www.thehindu.com/2001/09/05/stories/0205000t.htm |website=www.thehindu.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|Ram Subramanyam\n|January 2004\n|December 2005\n|[[Indian Army Corps of Engineers|Corps of Engineers]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=Lt-Gen Subramanyam is new GOC-in-C |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/lucknow/Lt-Gen-Subramanyam-is-new-GOC-in-C/articleshow/398910.cms |website=www.timesofindia.indiatimes.com |publisher=Times Of India}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|O P Nandrajog\n|January 2006\n|February 2008\n|[[Brigade of the Guards]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=Lt Gen Nandrajog takes over as Central Command GOC-in-C |url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newswire/story/lt-gen-nandrajog-takes-over-as-central-command-goc-in-c/345628 |website=www.outlookindia.com |publisher=Outlook}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|[[Harcharanjit Singh Panag|H S Panag]]\n|March 2008\n|December 2008\n|[[Mechanised Infantry Regiment]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=Senior Appointments : Army |url=http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=35568 |website=www.pib.nic.in |publisher=PIB}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|J K Mohanty\n|January 2009\n|February 2010\n|[[Dogra Regiment]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|[[Vijay Kumar Ahluwalia]]\n|March 2010\n|February 2012\n|[[Regiment of Artillery]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|[[Anil Chait]]\n|March 2012\n|June 2013\n|[[Indian Army Armoured Corps|Armoured Corps]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=LIEUTENANT GENERAL ANIL CHAIT TAKES OVER AS GOC-IN-C, CENTRAL COMMAND |url=https://indianarmy.nic.in/Site/PressRelease/frmPressRelease.aspx?n=bniEtbbo9LN7kb4q3kupGg==&NewsID=IEqoPZK7iFuiwWhYH0JH5w== |website=Indian Army}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|Rajan Bakhshi\n|July 2013\n|November 2015\n|[[Poona Horse]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=Lt Gen Rajan Bakhshi takes over as GOC-in-C, Central Command |url=http://www.indiandefencereview.com/news/lt-gen-rajan-bakhshi-takes-over-as-goc-in-c-central-command/ |website=Indian Defence Review}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|[[Balwant Singh Negi]]\n|December 2015\n|30 September 2018\n|[[Assam Regiment]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=Lt Gen BS Negi appointed Central Command\u2019s new GOC-in-C (designate) |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/lucknow/Lt-Gen-BS-Negi-appointed-Central-Commands-new-GOC-in-C-designate/articleshow/50068288.cms |website=Times of India}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|[[Abhay Krishna]]\n|1 October 2018\n|30 September 2019\n|[[Rajputana Rifles]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=Lt Gen Abhay Krishna takes over as GOC-in-Chief of Central Command - Times of India |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bareilly/lt-gen-abhay-krishna-takes-over-as-goc-in-chief-of-central-command/articleshow/66034681.cms |website=The Times of India}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|[[Iqroop Singh Ghuman]]\n|1 October 2019\n|Incumbent\n|[[Brigade of The Guards]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/defence/naravane-appointed-as-new-vice-chief-of-indian-army-four-army-commanders-appointed/articleshow/70339637.cms|title=Naravane appointed as new Vice Chief of Indian Army, four army commanders appointed|first1=Shaurya Karanbir|last1=Gurung|website=The Economic Times|accessdate=24 July 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n[[Operation Surya Hope]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.globalsecurity.org/military/world/india/centcom.htm Central Command @ globalsecurity.org]\n\n{{Indian Army Commands}}\n\n[[Category:Commands of the Indian Army]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian Army regional command}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=July 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2011}}\n{{Infobox military unit\n| unit_name = Central Command\n| image = IA Central Command.jpg\n| image_size = 200\n| caption = Central Command's insignia today\n| country = {{country|India}}\n| branch =  {{army|india}}\n| type = [[Formation (military)|Command]]\n| dates = 1942-1946<br>1 May 1963<ref name=\"TOI-20130503\">{{cite web | url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-05-03/lucknow/39008534_1_ex-servicemen-desh-seva-indian-army | title=Army pays poignant tributes to its martyrs & bravehearts | publisher=The Times of India | date=3 May 2013<!--, 05.04AM IST -->| accessdate=2013-06-21}}</ref> - Present\n| specialization = \n| command_structure = \n| size = \n| current_commander = Lt General [[Iqroop Singh Ghuman]], [[PVSM]], [[AVSM]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aninews.in/news/national/general-news/lt-general-is-ghuman-assumes-charge-as-commander-of-central-command-of-indian-army20191002141641/|title=Lt-General IS Ghuman assumes charge as Commander of Central Command of Indian Army|date=2019-10-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/cities/lt-gen-ghuman-takes-over-as-goc-in-c-of-central-command/story-5cfwPl5s1rnrHJdFzbvKpI.html|title=Lt Gen Ghuman takes over as GOC-in-C of Central Command|date=2019-10-02}}</ref>\n| garrison = [[Lucknow]], [[Uttar Pradesh]]\n| battles = \n| notable_commanders = \n}}\n\nThe '''Central Command''' of the [[Indian Army]] is one of the seven operational commands of the army. It is based at [[Lucknow]], [[Uttar Pradesh]].\nLt General [[Iqroop Singh Ghuman]] is the present [[General officer commanding|General Officer Commanding-in-Chief]].\n\n==History==\n===Pre WW-II===\nCentral Command was first established in 1942 during [[World War II]] and then disbanded in 1946.<ref name=\"Army Commands\">[http://www.gulabin.com/armynavy/pdf/Army%20Commands%201900-2011.pdf Army Commands] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150705211343/http://www.gulabin.com/armynavy/pdf/Army%20Commands%201900-2011.pdf |date=5 July 2015 }}</ref>\n[[Southern Command (India)|Southern Command]] was responsible for most of the training activities for Indian Army until Central Command was formed in April 1942 which took over the responsibility of some of the training areas.<ref name=\"IA-1939-47\">{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=w3BmOH-sac8C&pg=PT141&dq=central+command+of+indian+army&hl=en&sa=X&ei=XjvEUcPpLY_QrQeVtoGoAw&ved=0CEsQ6AEwBQ#v=onepage&q=central%20command&f=false | title=The Indian Army 1939-47 Experience and Development | publisher=Ashgate Publishing | date=1 Aug 2012 | accessdate=2013-06-21 |author1=Alan Jeffreys |author2=Patrick Rose }}</ref>\n\n===Post 1962 Indo-China war===\nWith its HQ at [[Lucknow]] the Command was re-established on 1 May 1963 due to the [[Sino-Indian War]] of 1962. Lt Gen K Bahadur Singh was the first Army Commander of the new Central Command. Prior to that date [[Lucknow]] had been the headquarters of the [[Eastern Command (India)|Eastern Command]].<ref name=\"TOI-2009-05-03\">{{cite web | url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-05-03/lucknow/28157520_1_ors-central-command-programmes | title=Central Command Raising Day concludes | publisher=The Times of India | date=3 May 2009<!--, 02.57am IST -->| accessdate=2013-06-21}}</ref><ref name=\"IE-CP\">{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FUjzWFsz5fwC&pg=PA3372&lpg=PA3372&dq=central+command+of+indian+army&source=bl&ots=s2z1Ch0N_I&sig=8EGR9U-reKQxidk7OeCUQ-zCYcU&hl=en&sa=X&ei=VjXEUbKMA4GJrAe83YDoDQ&ved=0CD8Q6AEwAzgo#v=onepage&q=central%20command%20of%20indian%20army&f=false | title=The Indian Encyclopaedia: India (Central Provinces)-Indology | publisher=Genesis Publishing Pvt Ltd | year=2002 | accessdate=2013-06-21 | author=Subodh Kapoor | pages=3372}}</ref>\n\n==Area and formations==\nCentral Commands spans across seven state of India:<ref name=\"TOI-20130503\"/>\n#[[Uttar Pradesh]]\n#[[Uttarakhand]]\n#[[Madhya Pradesh]]\n#[[Chhattisgarh]]\n#[[Bihar]]\n#[[Jharkhand]]\n#[[Odisha]]\n\nThere are two ''Static Area Foramations'' and one 6 ''Mountain Division'' under Central Command:<ref name=\"IAF\">{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=um22j1YWT0YC&pg=PA11&lpg=PA11&dq=central+command+of+indian+army&source=bl&ots=Nt7lom-yHE&sig=9F81vPgP7YNrYCuM9pdhBvtO2hQ&hl=en&sa=X&ei=pjfEUb7bAs6Wrgf_54HwCw&ved=0CDwQ6AEwAjgy#v=onepage&q=central%20command&f=false | title=Indian Armed Forces | publisher=Lancer Publishers | year=2008 | accessdate=2013-06-21 |author1=Bharat Verma |author2=G. M. Hiranandani |author3=B. K. Pandey | pages=16}}</ref>\n#Uttar Bharat Area headquartered at [[Bareilly]]\n#Madhya Bharat Area headquartered at [[Jabalpur]]\n#6 Mountain Division at [[Bareilly]] \n\n18 Regimental Centres and Large number of logistic and training establishments come under Central Command.  The responsibility for the central sector of the Western border with [[Pakistan]] also lies with Central Command.<ref name=\"GM-Com\">{{cite web | url=http://gomilitary.in/army/commands/ | title=Commands of the Indian Army | accessdate=2013-06-22 | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130602122132/http://gomilitary.in/army/commands/ | archivedate=2 June 2013 | df=dmy-all }}</ref> Almost half of the 62 [[cantonment]]s in India lie within the Central Command's theatre.<ref name=\"Hindu-2003-05-11\">{{cite web | url=http://www.hindu.com/2003/05/11/stories/2003051101731100.htm | title=Central Command's novel initiative | publisher=The Hindu | date=2003-05-11 | accessdate=2013-06-23 | author=Mukund Padmanabhan}}</ref>\n\n==Rescue operations during 2013 North India floods==\nDuring [[2013 North India floods]] in its rescue operations \"Operation Surya Hope\" in [[Uttarakhand]], the Central Command mobilised over 8,000 troops for rescue and relief operations for stranded people on all four different axis of Rishikesh-Uttarkashi-Harsil-Gangotri axis, Rudraprayag-Kedarnath axis, Joshimath-Badrinath axis and Dharchula-Tawaghat axis in Pithoragarh district. Under operation Ganga, the Army evacuated 1,150 persons from Harsil area; 6,000 from Joshimath and 700 from Tawaghat area. Army operations in the 40,000 square kilometres were led by Lieutenant General Anil Chait, General Officer Commanding-in-Chief, Central Command.<ref name=\"TOI-2013-06-19\">{{cite web | url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-06-19/lucknow/40068893_1_army-rescues-the-army-lieutenant-general-anil-chait | title=Army rescues over 7,000 stranded persons | publisher=The Times of India | date=19 Jun 2013<!--, 07.07 AM IST -->| accessdate=2013-06-21}}</ref><ref name=\"TOI-2013-06-21\">{{cite web | url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-06-21/lucknow/40117890_1_army-commander-axis-army-operations | title=2,500 additional troops deployed for rescue operations | publisher=The Times of India | date=21 Jun 2013<!--, 07.10 AM IST -->| accessdate=2013-06-21}}</ref>\n\n==Commanders prior to Independence==\nCommanders included:<ref name=\"Army Commands\"/>\n*1942-1944 Lieutenant-General [[Henry Willcox]]\n*1944-1946 General [[Geoffry Scoones|Sir Geoffry Scoones]]\n\n==List of Commanders==\n{{big|'''General Officer Commanding-in-Chief Central Command'''}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Rank\n!Name\n!Appointment Date\n!Left Office\n!Unit of Commission\n!References\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|[[Kanwar Bahadur Singh]]\n|May 1963\n|August 1966\n|[[19th Hyderabad Regiment]] (presently [[Kumaon Regiment]])\n|\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|[[Joginder Singh Dhillon]]\n|August 1966\n|August 1970\n|[[Bengal Engineer Group|Bengal Sappers]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|[[Premindra Singh Bhagat|P S Bhagat]]\n|August 1970\n|Jun 1972\n|[[Bombay Engineer Group|Bombay Sappers]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|H K Sibal\n|June 1972\n|November 1973\n|[[5 Gorkha Rifles (Frontier Force)]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|[[Khem Karan Singh|K K Singh]]\n|November 1973\n|March 1975\n|[[16th Light Cavalry]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=Lieutenant General Khem Karan Singh, MVC: A great military leader |url=http://www.defenceinfo.com/lieutenant-general-khem-karan-singh-mvc-a-great-military-leader |website=defenceinfo.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|J S Nakai\n|April 1975\n|March 1979\n|[[Regiment of Artillery]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=General Nakai laid to rest with service honours |url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2006/20060114/cth1.htm |website=tribuneindia.com |publisher=Tribune India}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|R D Hira\n|April 1979\n|June 1980\n|[[11 Gorkha Rifles]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|[[WAG Pinto]]\n|July 1980\n|June 1982\n|[[Brigade of the Guards]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|H C Dutta\n|July 1982\n|November 1983\n|[[8 Gorkha Rifles]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|Bhupinder Singh\n|December 1983\n|September 1985\n|[[Regiment of Artillery]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|K K Hazari\n|October 1985\n|January 1986\n|[[Regiment of Artillery]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|K B Mehta\n|February 1986\n|December 1987\n|[[Brigade of the Guards]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|[[Sami Khan (general)|Sami Khan]]\n|January 1988\n|March 1989\n|[[Madras Regiment|4 Madras]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|[[Sunith Francis Rodrigues|S F Rodrigues]]\n|April 1989\n|October 1989\n|[[Regiment of Artillery]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|[[F. N. Billimoria]]\n|November 1989\n|June 1991\n|[[5 Gorkha Rifles|2/5 Gorkha Rifles]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|Vijai Singh\n|July 1991\n|February 1992\n|[[8th Light Cavalry]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|Y N Sharma\n|March 1992\n|March 1994\n|[[The Grenadiers]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|Arun Gautam\n|April 1994\n|April 1995\n|[[Indian Army Armoured Corps|Armoured Corps]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|R K Gulati\n|April 1995\n|May 1996\n|[[9th Deccan Horse]]\n|\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|Chandra Sekhar\n|June 1996\n|September 1997\n|[[4 Gorkha Rifles|2/4 Gorkha Rifles]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=Padmanabhan may be new Army Chief |url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2000/20000801/main5.htm |website= |publisher=Tribune India}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|Surjit Singh\n|October 1997\n|September 2000\n|[[Dogra Regiment]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=\"Shortage of officers may continue\" |url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/2001/20011013/windows/main2.htm |website= |publisher=Tribune India}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|P S Joshi\n|October 2000\n|September 2001\n|[[8 Gorkha Rifles|1/8 Gorkha Rifles]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=First IDS chief Lt Gen Joshi dies |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/First-IDS-chief-Lt-Gen-Joshi-dies/articleshow/4729577.cms |website=Times of India |publisher=Times of India}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|D S Chauhan\n|October 2001\n|December 2003\n|[[Madras Regiment]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=New Army Vice-Chief |url=http://www.thehindu.com/2001/09/05/stories/0205000t.htm |website=www.thehindu.com}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Lieutenant General]]\n|Ram Subramanyam\n|January 2004\n|December 2005\n|[[Indian Army Corps of Engineers|Corps of Engineers]]\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=Lt-Gen Subramanyam is new GOC-in-C |url=https://timesofindia.